<h2><u>Saudi and it’s Indo-Pak Ties</u></h2>

Saudi has been the accepted leader of the Arabic world be it its economic stronghold or its religious sentiments being home to Mecca and Medina. Saudi has been one of the most important diplomatic partner of Pakistan but Pakistan is slowly but steadily losing its ties with the Saudi. Saudi too seems to align its interests the other way around, they have decided not to favor Pakistan just due to its religious similarities. After all one can’t simply live on the Saudi cash on the one side and on the other hand rebuking them publicly. This time even Saudi has decided to show its cards.<br><br>

Saudi has snubbed Pakistan halting its massive $6.2 Billion loan it gave Pakistan a couple of years back in 2018.Back then the newly elected Imran Khan government had managed the $6.2 Billion loan to keep the cash strapped nation running of which $3 Billion was parked by Saudi in their Reserve Bank and another $3.2 Billion in Oil. But as the recent developments say Saudi has called back $1 Billion from the fixed amount of $3 Billion and has also halted the $3.2 Billion Oil supplies with immediate effect. And as the sources suggest, the remaining $2 Billion can also be snatched by the Saudi very soon.<br><br>

Well this seemed quite obvious with motor-mouths like Qureshi and Fawad Ahmed Chaudhary in your government. <br><br>

<img class="d-block ml-auto mr-auto  img-fluid" style="border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #c0c0c0;margin-bottom:50px;" src="../post/pak-motormouth.jfif" alt="Pak’s Motor Mouths">
<p class="img-caption caption text-center" style="margin-top:-50px;font-size:0.8em;border-bottom:50px">Pakistan’s Fantastic Two’s</p>
 

Now as the Saudi has responded, Pakistan has started to feel the heat. Consequently, Pakistan Army  Chief General Qamar Javed Bajwa was on a visit to Saudi to mend the already bumbling strings between the two nations. Although they say that this trip was a pre-planned one to enhance the military ties between the two but even you know what’s the reality? <br><br>

And as they say “<i>Ab pachtaye hot kya, Jab chidiya chug gayi khet</i> ”. General Bajwa received a royal snub in the  Sheikhdom. He couldn’t even arrange a meeting with the Crown Prince Mohammad Bin Salman, forget about repairing the done damage.<br><br>

<h3><u>Increasing Arab-India Ties</u></h3>

As the Pakistan’s relations with the Arab Nations continues to deteriorate, on the same time the ties of these nations with India are on the rise. It has happened first time in history that the Arab nations are backing India on the Kashmir’s stand. Its like rubbing salt on already fresh wounds of Pakistan. Pakistan stands on the verge of OIC too and if you remember correctly in the previous OIC summit India was welcomed by the host UAE as an observer nation against the will of Pakistan. This has been a significant Geo-political win for India. Many Muslim majority countries now withstands India with the only exception of Turkey  and Malaysia.<br><br>

 The Arab nations are further looking to boost their ties with India be it trade deals, defense cooperation, intelligence sharing or honoring our PM with their highest Civilian Award.<br><br>

<img class="d-block ml-auto mr-auto  img-fluid" style="border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #c0c0c0;margin-bottom:50px;" src="../post/pak-modi-uae.jfif" alt="UAE">
<p class="img-caption caption text-center" style="margin-top:-50px;font-size:0.8em;border-bottom:50px">PM Modi being honored by UAE</p>
 

<h2><u>Conclusion</u></h2>

These changes mark the changing geopolitics in the Western Asia. While Pakistan’s Obsession for Kashmir has made sure no Arab nation or otherwise any nation stands by it. On the other hand the gap between India and the middle-east has been shrinking continuously at an unprecedented rate.<br><br>

Just see the most recent development of setting up of diplomatic relations between UAE and the Israel, the relations marking the beginning of a new era. The era of peace and harmony in West-Asia.<br><br>

